{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Superwall is built on 3 core principles:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Triggers"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rules"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paywalls"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When your app executes a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"trigger"}]},{"type":"text","text":", evaluate a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rule"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to decide which "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"paywall"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to show the user."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Triggers and Rules are grouped in a concept we call "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Campaigns"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Rapid-Iteration","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rapid Iteration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paywalls and Campaigns are all defined in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/superwall.com\/dashboard"},{"type":"text","text":". If you don’t already have a Superwall account, you can "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/superwall.com\/sign-up"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Integrating the Paywall SDK into your app is usually the last time you’ll have to write paywall related code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This allows you to iterate on 5 key aspects of your monetization flow, without shipping app updates:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Design"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Text \/ Copy"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Placement"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pricing"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Discounts"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paywalls"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Superwall uses a script called "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paywall.js"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to turn websites into paywall templates. The Paywall SDK loads these websites inside a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIWebView"},{"type":"text","text":", and executes javascript on them to replace text and template product information. This gives you the flexibility to turn any design into a paywall and update it remotely."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since building websites can be tedious, Superwall maintains a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/webflow.com\/website\/45-Paywall-Elements?ref=showcase-search&searchValue=superwall"},{"type":"text","text":" including ~50 of the most prominent paywall elements we’ve seen across thousands of apps."}]},{"anchor":"Rules","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rules"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rules allow you to conditionally show a paywall to a user. For example, you may want to only show users paywalls if they have no remaining credits or if their account is over 24 hours old."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rule evaluations happen client side, so no network requests are fired to determine whether or not to show a paywall."}]},{"anchor":"Triggers","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Triggers"},{"